# Repo-root build-context excludes, honored by BOTH the classic builder and
# BuildKit. Per-Dockerfile `<Dockerfile>.dockerignore` files are a BuildKit-only
# feature, so they are silently ignored when a build runs under the classic
# builder (e.g. the standalone `docker-compose` binary that bench/run.sh may fall
# back to). Keeping the rules here makes them builder-independent.
#
# Critically for bench/Dockerfile.linux-arm64: this keeps the host's build
# artifacts (**/bin, **/obj — restored/compiled for osx-arm64) out of the
# linux/arm64 bench image's context on every path, so the `COPY . .` can't drag a
# foreign-RID restore state into the container. It also trims every image build's
# context.
#
# MUST NOT exclude publish/ — ./Dockerfile (the Server image) COPYs its payload
# from publish/arm64/, so that path has to remain in the build context.
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/.vs/
**/*.user
.git/
.github/
OpenAstroAra.Client/
docs/
design/
**/*.md
bench/
